  "answer_format": "numeric_decimal",
  "solution": "**Step 1: Define Key Variables**: Cash Flows = {Year 1: $150,000, Year 2: $200,000, Year 3: $250,000}; Discount Rate = 8%. <br> **Step 2: Calculate Present Values**: PV Year 1 = $150,000 / (1 + 0.08)^1 = $138,888.89; PV Year 2 = $200,000 / (1 + 0.08)^2 = $171,467.76; PV Year 3 = $250,000 / (1 + 0.08)^3 = $197,530.87. <br> **Step 3: Calculate NPV**: NPV = PV Year 1 + PV Year 2 + PV Year 3 = $138,888.89 + $171,467.76 + $197,530.87 = $526,931.64."
